* Command-line options::        All available flags
* Environment variable::        The most common invocation method
* Capturing output::            Reading widget values in a script
* Output formats::              Bash, JSON, and XML output
* Reading from a file::         Loading the dialog from a file
* Standard input::              Piping the dialog via stdin
* Including function libraries:: Sourcing shell functions for actions
* Multiple windows::            Working with more than one window
* Layout options::              Controlling widget packing defaults
* Window placement::            Setting window position and size


