5 Widgets
*********

The dialog description language is a simple XML-like markup capable of
describing complex dialog boxes containing widgets and containers.

   Widgets are GUI elements such as buttons, entry fields, lists, and
labels.  Every widget can have attributes, states, and actions (*note
Actions::).  Widgets must be placed inside containers (*note
Containers::).

   Most widgets support the following common sub-elements:

‘<variable>’
     Names the shell variable that receives this widget's value on exit.
‘<label>’
     Sets the display text.
‘<default>’
     Sets the initial value.
‘<input>’
     A shell command whose output sets the widget's value.
‘<input file>’
     A file whose contents set the widget's value.
‘<output file>’
     A file to write the widget's value to (used with ‘save:’).
‘<action>’
     A command to run when the widget changes (*note Actions::).
‘<sensitive>’
     Sets the initial interactive state (‘enabled’ or ‘disabled’).
‘<width>, <height>’
     Sets the widget's minimum size.

* Menu:

* text::                Static text labels
* button::              Pushbuttons
* entry::               Single-line text input
* checkbox::            On/off check marks
* radiobutton::         Mutually exclusive choices
* togglebutton::        Toggle buttons with icon support
* switch::              On/off slide switch
* combobox::            Drop-down selection (editable)
* comboboxtext::        Drop-down selection (fixed choices)
* comboboxentry::       Drop-down with editable entry
* list::                Single-column selection list
* table::               Multi-column sortable table
* tree::                Multi-column tree view
* edit::                Multi-line text editor
* pixmap::              Static image display
* hscale and vscale::   Slider controls
* spinbutton::          Numeric entry with up/down arrows
* colorbutton::         Colour picker button
* fontbutton::          Font picker button
* progressbar::         Progress indicator
* statusbar::           Status message bar
* timer::               Periodic timer
* hseparator and vseparator::  Decorative separator lines
* menubar::             Menu bar with drop-down menus
* terminal::            Embedded terminal emulator
* sourceview::          Syntax-highlighting text editor
* webview::             Embedded web browser


